      "content": "right, but some people say the \"social variables\" argument is just a way to handwave away the actual data. if you look at researchers like Jensen or Murray, they're pretty blunt about saying the math shows a biological basis for these racial gaps. can u actually layout what those specific proponents conclude about the hierarchy of group intelligence? i'm looking for a more direct explanation of their position on how different groups rank in terms of cognitive ability.",
